ğŸ”‘ 3 Main Transition Strategies
1ï¸âƒ£ Dual Stack

        Device/Router dono protocols samajhta hai â†’ IPv4 bhi aur IPv6 bhi ek sath.
        
        Matlab ek hi system me do alag address hote hain.
        
        Agar saamne wala IPv4 pe hai to IPv4 se baat hogi, agar IPv6 pe hai to IPv6 se baat hogi.

ğŸ‘‰ Example (Hindi):
        Soch tu ek banda hai jo Hindi aur English dono bol leta hai.
        
        Agar saamne wala Hindi bolta hai â†’ tu Hindi me reply deta hai.
        
        Agar English bolta hai â†’ tu English me reply deta hai.

âš¡ Ye sabse zyada flexible aur recommended approach hai.

2ï¸âƒ£ Tunneling

        Agar network IPv4 ka hai, par tu IPv6 ka data bhejna chahta hai, to us IPv6 packet ko IPv4 ke andar pack (encapsulate) karke bhej dete hain.
        
        Matlab ek tarah ka cover chadha dena.

ğŸ‘‰ Example:
        Soch tu ek gift (IPv6 packet) bhej raha hai par courier company sirf brown box (IPv4) accept karti hai.
        
        Tu gift ko brown box me pack karke bhejta hai.
        
        Dusre side pe brown box khola jaata hai aur asli gift (IPv6 packet) nikalta hai.

âš¡ Isse IPv6 traffic easily IPv4 network ke through travel kar leta hai.

3ï¸âƒ£ Translation (NAT64 / DNS64)

        Jab ek device sirf IPv6 pe hai aur dusra sirf IPv4 pe hai â†’ to unke beech ek translator lagta hai.
        
        Ye IPv6 ko IPv4 me convert karta hai aur vice versa.

ğŸ‘‰ Example:
        Soch ek banda sirf Hindi jaanta hai aur dusra sirf English.
        
        Beech me ek translator (NAT64) hai jo Hindi â†” English translate karta hai.
        
        Dono easily communicate kar lete hain.

âš¡ Ye un situations me useful hai jaha dual stack possible nahi hota.

ğŸ“ Summary (Easy Yaad Rakhne ka Tarika)

        Dual Stack â†’ Dono languages bolne wala banda (IPv4 + IPv6).
        
        Tunneling â†’ Gift ko dusre box me pack karke bhejna.

Translation â†’ Beech me translator jo convert karta hai.
